Description: Lip sherd of Attic black-figured pottery cup-skyphos; interior glazed with reserved line at lip; exterior of lip black; below, frieze with traces of black-figure decoration, perhaps a head; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 468)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0725) (Phase 1)
